      "web_research": {
        "results": [
          {
            "possibleIdentity": "Glenn Steigelman is a photographer and artist who has been active in the New York art world since at least the late 1960s. He is best known for his extensive documentation of major contemporary artists and their works, particularly those of Robert Rauschenberg, with whom he had a long-standing professional relationship. Steigelman's photographs are frequently cited in the archives of the Robert Rauschenberg Foundation and have appeared in numerous major museum catalogs, including those for the Museum of Modern Art (MoMA). Beyond documentation, he was a participant in the collaborative group Ocean Earth (also known as Ocean Earth Construction & Development or OECD) and was featured in the 1982 exhibition 'Space Force - OECD' at Galerie Peter Pakesch in Vienna. His early career included work for Andy Warhol's Interview Magazine, with credits dating back to November 1969. His association with Experiments in Art and Technology (E.A.T.) is supported by his close proximity to Rauschenberg (a co-founder of E.A.T.) and his participation in technology-oriented and multidisciplinary art groups like Ocean Earth.",
            "sources": [
              "https://www.rauschenbergfoundation.org/art/archives/photograph-collection/hoarfrosts-guild-hall",
